### Describe the bug

Decorator beans do not appear in the list of beans nor in the list of removed beans.

### Expected behavior

Decorator beans should appear in both lists as appropriate, just like Interceptor beans do.

### Actual behavior

Interceptors appear (even have their own graphical list in dev console UI), decorators do not.

### How to Reproduce?

Define a Bean with an interface and a decorator for said interface, e.g.
```
public interface EventCollector {

    List<Object> getFiredEvents();

    <T> void collect(T event);
}


@ApplicationScoped
@Unremovable
public class EventCollectorImpl implements EventCollector {

    List<Object> firedEvents = new ArrayList<>();

    @Override
    public List<Object> getFiredEvents() {
        return firedEvents;
    }

    @Override
    public <T> void collect(final T event) {
        firedEvents.add(event);
    }
}

@Decorator
@Priority(Interceptor.Priority.APPLICATION)
public abstract class EventCollectorDecorator implements EventCollector {

    @Inject
    @Delegate
    @Any
    EventCollector delegate;
}
```
The run quarkus:dev and look in /q/arc/beans, /q/arc/removed-beans, /q/dev/io.quarkus.quarkus-arc/beans, and /q/dev/io.quarkus.quarkus-arc/removed-beans for the decorator.

